---
export const prerender = true;
import BlogLayout from '../../layouts/BlogLayout.astro';
import '../../styles/global.css';
---

<BlogLayout
  title="Best X Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring X Plays"
  description="Master the best X words in Scrabble with our free ranked list. Top scoring X plays with point values, short X words, and premium square strategy tips."
  keywords="best x words scrabble, x words scrabble, high scoring x words, scrabble x strategy, maximize scrabble, oxygen scrabble points"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "Article",
    "headline": "Best X Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring X Plays",
    "description": "Master the best X words in Scrabble with ranked list, point values, and strategy tips.",
    "datePublished": "2026-06-14",
    "author": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com", "url": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com" },
    "publisher": { "@type": "Organization", "name": "ScrabbleWordsFinder.com" },
    "mainEntityOfPage": { "@type": "WebPage", "@id": "https://www.scrabblewordsfinder.com/blog/best-x-words-scrabble" }
  })} />

  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify({
    "@context": "https://schema.org",
    "@type": "FAQPage",
    "mainEntity": [
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What is the best X word in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "OXYPHENBUTAZONE scores 41 points as the theoretical best. For practical play, MAXIMIZE scores 28 points, EXACTLY scores 19 points, and HEXAGON/JINX/SPHINX each score 18 points. X is worth 8 points per tile." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "What are the best two-letter X words in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "AX, EX, OX, and XI all score 9 points each. These are among the highest-scoring two-letter words in Scrabble and are essential for parallel plays, tight board positions, and reaching premium squares." }
      },
      {
        "@type": "Question",
        "name": "Should you ever exchange X in Scrabble?",
        "acceptedAnswer": { "@type": "Answer", "text": "Never exchange X. With four two-letter words available (AX, EX, OX, XI — all scoring 9 points), X always has a valid high-scoring play. Even in the worst position, you can score 9+ points. Hold X and wait for premium square access." }
      }
    ]
  })} />

  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-12">
    <article class="prose prose-invert prose-gray max-w-none">
      <nav class="text-sm text-gray-400 mb-6 not-prose flex items-center gap-1">
        <a href="/blog/" class="hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Blog</a>
        <span class="mx-1">›</span>
        <span class="text-gray-300">High-Scoring Words</span>
      </nav>

      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white mb-4">Best X Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring X Plays</h1>

      <div class="not-prose mb-8 flex items-center gap-3 text-sm text-gray-400">
        <time datetime="2026-06-14">June 14, 2026</time>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <span>5 min read</span>
        <span class="w-1 h-1 rounded-full bg-gray-600"></span>
        <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-blue-400 hover:underline"><span aria-hidden="true">🔤</span> Word Finder</a>
      </div>

      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-gray-300 mb-8">
        X is arguably the best tile in Scrabble relative to its difficulty. Worth 8 points (third-highest after Q and Z), X doesn't need any specific companion letter and has four two-letter plays as fallbacks. From monster words like MAXIMIZE to surgical strikes with AX or OX, X is the most versatile premium tile in the game.
      </p>

      <!-- Hero Card -->
      <div class="not-prose my-8 p-6 rounded-2xl border-2 border-amber-500/50 bg-gradient-to-r from-amber-950/30 to-yellow-950/20 relative overflow-hidden">
        <div class="absolute top-3 right-4 text-xs font-bold uppercase tracking-widest text-amber-500/70">👑 X TILE</div>
        <p class="text-2xl font-black text-white tracking-wider mb-2">MOST VERSATILE PREMIUM TILE</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-amber-300 font-semibold mb-3">8 points • 4 two-letter fallbacks • Never gets stuck</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">X has the best risk-to-reward ratio of any premium tile. Four guaranteed 9-point plays (AX, EX, OX, XI) mean you always have a strong option, while longer X words like MAXIMIZE (28 pts) deliver massive scores.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Stat Strip -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-cyan-500/30 bg-cyan-950/10">
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-6 text-center">
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">8 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Tile value</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">1</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">In the bag</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">4</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Two-letter words</p></div>
          <div><p class="text-xl font-bold text-cyan-400">28 pts</p><p class="text-xs text-gray-400">MAXIMIZE (best practical)</p></div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Top 10 Best X Words for Scrabble</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">These are the highest-scoring X words, ranked by base point value. X's versatility means you'll find strong plays at every word length.</p>

      <div class="overflow-x-auto not-prose my-6">
        <table class="w-full text-sm border border-gray-700 rounded-lg overflow-hidden shadow-sm">
          <thead class="bg-gray-800">
            <tr>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">#</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Word</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Points</th>
              <th class="px-4 py-3 text-left font-semibold text-gray-300">Length</th>
            </tr>
          </thead>
          <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-800">
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">1</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYPHENBUTAZONE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">41</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">15</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">2</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">MAXIMIZE</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">28</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">3</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXACTLY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">19</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">HEXAGON</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">JINX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">4</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">SPHINX</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">18</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">7</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">OXYGEN</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">8</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">GALAXY</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">17</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-900"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">9</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">EXOTIC</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">15</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">6</td></tr>
            <tr class="bg-gray-800/50"><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">10</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-white font-medium">PIXEL</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-blue-400">14</td><td class="px-4 py-3 text-gray-400">5</td></tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>

      <!-- Insight Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-blue-500/30 bg-blue-950/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Efficiency King</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">JINX scores <span class="text-white font-medium">18 points in just 4 letters</span> (4.5 pts/letter) — pairing X with J for two premium tiles in a short word. On a double word score, that's 36 points from a word that fits anywhere.</p>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Why X Is the Most Versatile Premium Tile</h2>
      <p class="text-gray-300">X holds a unique position in Scrabble — it's the third most valuable tile at 8 points, but it's arguably the easiest premium tile to play. Unlike Q (which usually needs U) and Z (which has limited two-letter options), X has four two-letter words: AX, EX, OX, and XI. Each scores 9 points, giving you a guaranteed high-scoring fallback in any board position.</p>

      <!-- Comparison Cards: X vs Q vs Z -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
          <p class="text-green-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✓ X Advantages Over Q & Z</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">4 two-letter fallbacks (vs Z's 2 and Q's 1). No companion letter needed. EX- prefix gives dozens of options. Never needs exchanging. Works at every word length.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-red-500/30 bg-red-950/10">
          <p class="text-red-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-1">✗ X Limitations</p>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Only 8 points (vs Q/Z at 10). No double-X words in standard play. Maximum base score lower than PIZZAZZ (45) or SQUEEZE (25). Fewer surprise factor plays.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <p class="text-gray-300">Beyond the two-letter plays, X appears in an enormous range of common English words. The EX- prefix alone gives you EXACTLY (19 pts), EXOTIC (15 pts), EXCLAIM, EXPIRY, and dozens more. MAXIMIZE (28 pts) combines X with Z for the ultimate premium tile pairing.</p>

      <!-- Pill Badges: Two-Letter X Words -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3 text-center">Your 4 Guaranteed Fallbacks (9 pts each)</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-3">
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">AX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9 pts</span>
          </span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">EX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9 pts</span>
          </span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">OX</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9 pts</span>
          </span>
          <span class="inline-flex items-center gap-1.5 px-3 py-1.5 rounded-lg bg-gray-800 border border-gray-700 text-sm">
            <span class="text-white font-bold">XI</span><span class="text-amber-400 text-xs">9 pts</span>
          </span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Inline Cross-Links -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-4 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-3">📚 Dig Deeper</p>
        <div class="grid gap-2">
          <a href="/blog/words-containing-x/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Words Containing X — the full list beyond just the top scorers</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-words-for-premium-squares/" class="flex items-center gap-2 p-2 rounded-lg hover:bg-indigo-900/20 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-indigo-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform shrink-0">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-indigo-300 transition-colors">Best Words for Premium Squares — maximize your DLS, TLS, DWS, TWS plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-blue-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-blue-400 pl-4">Strategy Tips — Maximizing X Value</h2>

      <!-- Purple Strategy Tips -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Four two-letter fallbacks:</span> AX, EX, OX, XI — all score 9 points. X is never stuck because you always have a 9-point minimum play available.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">JINX is the most efficient X word:</span> 18 points in 4 letters = 4.5 pts/letter. It pairs X with J for a devastating short play that fits tight positions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">X on premium squares:</span> X on DLS = 16 points, X on TLS = 24 points from one tile. Short X words like AX and OX are perfect for reaching these squares.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">EX- prefix is your best friend:</span> EXACTLY, EXOTIC, EXCLAIM, EXPIRY — the EX- prefix opens up dozens of options from common rack letters.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-purple-500/30 bg-purple-950/20 hover:border-purple-400 transition-colors">
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300"><span class="text-purple-400 font-semibold">Never exchange X:</span> With four 9-point two-letter plays always available, there's never a reason to exchange X. Hold it for premium square access.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Premium Square Math -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-green-500/30 bg-green-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 Premium Square Math</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AX on DLS = <span class="text-white font-medium">17 points</span> (X doubled to 16 + A = 1). OX on TLS = <span class="text-white font-medium">25 points</span> (X tripled to 24 + O = 1). JINX on DWS = <span class="text-white font-medium">36 points</span>. X makes even 2-letter plays score like full words.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Warning Callout -->
      <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">⚠️ Don't Settle</p>
        <p class="text-base text-gray-200">AX/EX/OX are <span class="text-white font-medium">fallbacks, not goals</span>. Always scan for EXACTLY, HEXAGON, JINX, OXYGEN first. Only use 2-letter plays when the board truly blocks longer options or you need a specific tactical play.</p>
      </div>

      <!-- Related Articles -->
      <aside class="border-t border-gray-700 mt-12 pt-8 not-prose">
        <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-gray-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
        <div class="grid gap-3">
          <a href="/blog/highest-scoring-scrabble-words/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Highest Scoring Scrabble Words Ever — Ultimate List</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-j-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best J Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring J Plays</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/blog/best-z-words-scrabble/" class="flex items-center gap-3 p-3 rounded-lg border border-gray-800 hover:border-blue-700 hover:bg-blue-900/10 transition-all group">
            <span class="text-blue-400 group-hover:translate-x-0.5 transition-transform">→</span>
            <span class="text-sm text-gray-300 group-hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">Best Z Words in Scrabble — Top Scoring Z Plays</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="not-prose mt-10 p-5 bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-900/20 to-indigo-900/20 border border-blue-800 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between gap-4 flex-wrap">
          <p class="text-sm text-blue-300 font-medium">🔤 Test your X words with our free solver — instant results, no signup</p>
          <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg bg-blue-600 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white text-sm font-semibold transition-colors shadow-sm">Open Word Finder →</a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="not-prose mt-8 text-center">
        <a href="/blog/" class="text-sm text-gray-400 hover:text-blue-400 transition-colors">← Back to all articles</a>
      </div>
    </article>
  </div>
</BlogLayout>
